28
00:01:05,883 --> 00:01:09,210
that have made me the
successful person I am today.

29
00:01:09,210 --> 00:01:11,190
Stage one, the awakening.

30
00:01:11,190 --> 00:01:14,400
This is when I went from 0 to $20,000.

31
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:17,520
My journey started as I
emerged from my mother's womb

32
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:20,460
and my first words were,
which stocks should I buy?

33
00:01:20,460 --> 00:01:21,293
Just kidding.

34
00:01:21,293 --> 00:01:23,250
Like most people, I was pretty clueless

35
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:25,230
about financial education as a kid,

36
00:01:25,230 --> 00:01:27,060
but I had the spirit of hustle in me.

37
00:01:27,060 --> 00:01:29,400
One of my earliest memories
of entrepreneurship

38
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:32,010
goes back to when I was
selling fish door to door.

39
00:01:32,010 --> 00:01:34,320
Just imagine wiping the sleep dust

40
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:36,390
out of your eyes at four in the morning,

41
00:01:36,390 --> 00:01:39,390
heading down to a freezing
pier and sitting for hours

42
00:01:39,390 --> 00:01:42,150
until you'd caught enough
mackerel to sell for a profit.

43
00:01:42,150 --> 00:01:42,983
Not only that

44
00:01:42,983 --> 00:01:46,650
but grabbing a slimy fish from
a bag, ringing a doorbell,

45
00:01:46,650 --> 00:01:49,410
looking a person straight in
the eye and pitching to them.

46
00:01:49,410 --> 00:01:51,750
This built up my confidence
and sales skills.

47
00:01:51,750 --> 00:01:54,210
Two of the earlier
skills I needed to learn

48
00:01:54,210 --> 00:01:55,320
to be successful.

49
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:56,153
As I earned,

50
00:01:56,153 --> 00:01:59,070
I soon found that any money
I made wasn't really mine.

51
00:01:59,070 --> 00:02:01,590
Instead it would go places like McDonald's

52
00:02:01,590 --> 00:02:03,540
and the girl I happened to be dating.

53
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:05,730
I always seem to have just enough.

54
00:02:05,730 --> 00:02:07,590
This is called lifestyle inflation,

55
00:02:07,590 --> 00:02:10,260
the tendency to spend
more as you make more.

56
00:02:10,260 --> 00:02:11,130
Whatever you earn,

57
00:02:11,130 --> 00:02:14,130
it becomes your new baseline,
and that's the trap.

58
00:02:14,130 --> 00:02:15,660
But being a car fanatic,

59
00:02:15,660 --> 00:02:17,940
I've always dreamed of owning a Ferrari.

60
00:02:17,940 --> 00:02:20,250
I felt as if they sent
such a strong signal

61
00:02:20,250 --> 00:02:21,630
to others that you've made it.

62
00:02:21,630 --> 00:02:23,310
I'd often speak to my friend Paul

63
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:26,940
who worked as a valet parking
cars for the rich and famous.

64
00:02:26,940 --> 00:02:28,170
He once told me something

65
00:02:28,170 --> 00:02:30,510
that changed my perspective on luxuries.

66
00:02:30,510 --> 00:02:33,390
He said, when people would
drive up to the hotel

67
00:02:33,390 --> 00:02:35,820
in their Ferraris, they
would watch me gawk

68
00:02:35,820 --> 00:02:37,410
and love every moment of it.

69
00:02:37,410 --> 00:02:40,950
I'm sure they felt admired,
important, even respected

70
00:02:40,950 --> 00:02:42,780
but actually, you know what, Mark?

71
00:02:42,780 --> 00:02:45,660
I didn't care about them
or even notice them.

72
00:02:45,660 --> 00:02:48,030
Instead, I thought,
wow, if I had that car,

73
00:02:48,030 --> 00:02:49,500
people would think I'm cool.

74
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,570
And I wonder how many
people buy these cars

75
00:02:51,570 --> 00:02:54,270
without realizing that
people rarely give the driver

76
00:02:54,270 --> 00:02:55,500
a moment's thought.

77
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:56,333
I learned

78
00:02:56,333 --> 00:02:58,860
that no one would be as
impressed with my possessions

79
00:02:58,860 --> 00:03:00,510
and luxuries as much as me.

80
00:03:00,510 --> 00:03:01,980
People want to be respected

81
00:03:01,980 --> 00:03:05,370
and admired by others, but
competence, intelligence

82
00:03:05,370 --> 00:03:08,340
and kindness will bring
you so much more respect

83
00:03:08,340 --> 00:03:09,840
than horsepower ever will.

84
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:11,940
With all the information
out there on the internet

85
00:03:11,940 --> 00:03:13,980
about how to make money or get rich quick,

86
00:03:13,980 --> 00:03:15,870
it can be hard to separate the truth

87
00:03:15,870 --> 00:03:16,860
from the marketing.

88
00:03:16,860 --> 00:03:19,860
Internet gurus have been getting
wealthy for the past decade

89
00:03:19,860 --> 00:03:22,350
telling other people how they can get rich

90
00:03:22,350 --> 00:03:25,350
and there's a whole industry
out there based on fantasy,

91
00:03:25,350 --> 00:03:28,020
but the truth is wealth
is not always what you see

92
00:03:28,020 --> 00:03:29,370
but what you don't see.

93
00:03:29,370 --> 00:03:33,000
I decided instead, I'd quietly
follow my own path to wealth,

94
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:35,970
but in order to do
this, I needed a budget.

95
00:03:35,970 --> 00:03:38,070
A budget is knowing
where your money will go

96
00:03:38,070 --> 00:03:39,900
versus where it went.

97
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:42,000
Little by little and for the first time,

98
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,460
I started seeing my savings account go up.

99
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:46,680
I started building an emergency fund,

100
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:49,050
basically money for a rainy day.

101
00:03:49,050 --> 00:03:51,570
I didn't know exactly
when or why it would rain

102
00:03:51,570 --> 00:03:53,280
only that one day it would.

103
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:55,020
One day my boss approached me

104
00:03:55,020 --> 00:03:58,080
