putting yourself out there,

226
00:08:28,890 --> 00:08:30,870
but keeping money requires the opposite.

227
00:08:30,870 --> 00:08:32,700
It requires humility and fear

228
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:34,680
that what you've made can be taken away

229
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:36,960
from you just like that.

230
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:39,210
Once you lose 95% of your money,

231
00:08:39,210 --> 00:08:42,390
you have to gain 1900%

232
00:08:42,390 --> 00:08:44,460
just to get back to where you started.

233
00:08:44,460 --> 00:08:46,950
Taking too much risk can bury you so deep

234
00:08:46,950 --> 00:08:49,740
in a hole it can be nearly
impossible to get out of.

235
00:08:49,740 --> 00:08:52,140
I even started to move
my operations online

236
00:08:52,140 --> 00:08:54,120
to adapt to the changing times.

237
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,950
Stage three, the trap.

238
00:08:55,950 --> 00:09:00,000
This is when I went from
$100,000 to $1 million.

239
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,010
I realized that one of
the biggest problems

240
00:09:02,010 --> 00:09:04,036
people face is when
they turn their passion

241
00:09:04,036 --> 00:09:06,720
into a vehicle to accumulate money.

242
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:09,390
They are now reliant on it
to fund their lifestyle,

243
00:09:09,390 --> 00:09:11,730
leading to their passion
becoming their prison.

244
00:09:11,730 --> 00:09:13,020
I mean, the biggest bottleneck

245
00:09:13,020 --> 00:09:15,960
in my business was actually
the business owner, me.

246
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:17,370
As the business got bigger

247
00:09:17,370 --> 00:09:19,320
and as we tried to move it online,

248
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:21,720
so did the number of problems, complaints

249
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:23,700
and things to worry about.

250
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:26,310
It always seems like as
soon as I solved a problem,

251
00:09:26,310 --> 00:09:28,020
another one would soon follow.

252
00:09:28,020 --> 00:09:31,050
Don't get me wrong, owning and
running a business is great,

253
00:09:31,050 --> 00:09:33,150
especially if you are passionate about it,

254
00:09:33,150 --> 00:09:34,890
but it isn't as easy or as passive

255
00:09:34,890 --> 00:09:36,600
as a lot of people make it out to be.

256
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,700
I've read a lot of books on investing,

257
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:41,310
studied the techniques of Warren Buffet

258
00:09:41,310 --> 00:09:43,290
and come across John Bogle's book

259
00:09:43,290 --> 00:09:44,970
about common sense investing.

260
00:09:44,970 --> 00:09:46,530
It shocked me when I learned

261
00:09:46,530 --> 00:09:50,490
that 80% of active fund
managers actually underperform

262
00:09:50,490 --> 00:09:52,408
the S&P 500 Index.

263
00:09:52,408 --> 00:09:55,620
Diversification is important
and buying and investing

264
00:09:55,620 --> 00:10:00,620
in the S&P 500, which is
a basket of 503 stocks,

265
00:10:00,630 --> 00:10:02,730
I could earn a steady growth that grows

266
00:10:02,730 --> 00:10:04,290
along with the US economy.

267
00:10:04,290 --> 00:10:06,060
My goal was to have enough money

268
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:09,990
in the S&P 500 that in
the worst case scenario,

269
00:10:09,990 --> 00:10:13,500
I could withdraw up to 4%
per year in order to live

270
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:16,770
off my investments while
still growing my portfolio.

271
00:10:16,770 --> 00:10:19,830
By sticking to my guns, I
was able to avoid suffering

272
00:10:19,830 --> 00:10:22,560
from the internet stock crash of 2000.

273
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:23,700
Early on in my journey,

274
00:10:23,700 --> 00:10:25,740
I learned that the losses felt massive

275
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:28,200
whereas a profit seemed so, so slow.

276
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:30,120
There's an old saying, stocks rise

277
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:32,820
like an escalator and
crash like an elevator,

278
00:10:32,820 --> 00:10:34,560
and this couldn't be more true.

279
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:36,240
I kept dollar cost averaging

280
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:38,520
and adding to my stock portfolio,

281
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:41,310
even as the .com crash continued.

282
00:10:41,310 --> 00:10:43,800
I was getting more and more
shares of the index fund

283
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:45,660
at better and better prices.

284
00:10:45,660 --> 00:10:48,660
As a qualified pilot,
I draw this parallel,

285
00:10:48,660 --> 00:10:51,330
hours and hours of uneventful flight

286
00:10:51,330 --> 00:10:53,550
followed by moments of sheer terror,

287
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:55,410
but it's these moments of sheer terror

288
00:10:55,410 --> 00:10:57,960
that make up the majority of your returns.

289
00:10:57,960 --> 00:11:01,410
The way I conducted my
finances during the .com crash

290
00:11:01,410 --> 00:11:05,370
and the 2008 financial
crisis gave me more returns

291
00:11:05,370 --> 00:11:07,860
than any investing I'd ever done before.

292
00:11:07,860 --> 00:11:09,840
Stage four, the refinement.

293
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:13,140
This is when I went from
$1 million to $10 million.

294
00:11:13,140 --> 00:11:15,600
As my wealth grew, it
seemed like the matrix

295
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,700
was creating more and more temptations

296
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:19,770
to take my money away from me.

297
00:11:19,770 --> 00:11:22,050
Having savings gives you a lot of options

298
00:11:22,050 --> 00:11:24,900
like going to a buffet where
you can have every dish

299
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:25,980
you've ever wanted.

300
00:11:25,980 --> 00:11:27,300
In the previous stages,

301
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:30,810
once I'd surpassed a
$100,000 in yearly earnings,

302
00:11:30,810 --> 00:11:33,540
I was considered an accredited investor,

303
00:11:33,540 --> 00:11:36,780
which is both an exciting
and a dangerous place to be.

304
00:11:36,780 --> 00:11:40,110
I fell into the trap of
investing in various penny stocks

305
00:11:40,110 --> 00:11:42,480
which initially was very successful.

306
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:45,540
However, I went on to lose $30,000

307
00:11:45,540 --> 00:11:47,280
with a couple of bad trades.

308
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:49,710
After this, I created a rule for myself

309
00:11:49,710 --> 00:11:52,890
to only invest in things
that I fully understand,

310
00:11:52,890 --> 00:11:55,740
unless it's an experiment
with a small amount of capital

311
00:11:55,740 --> 00:11:57,300
that I'm not afraid to lose.

312
00:11:57,300 --> 00:11:59,100
It doesn't matter
whether you are investing

313
00:11:59,100 --> 00:12:01,973
in NFTs, stocks or a relationship,

314
00:12:01,973 --> 00:12:04,260
I learned to always do my homework

315
00:12:04,260 --> 00:12:07,410
and take the time to
understand every opportunity.

316
00:12:07,410 --> 00:12:10,650
The thing I understood more
than anything was my business.

317
00:12:10,650 --> 00:12:13,740
I wanted to really push forward,
so I flew out to America

318
00:12:13,740 --> 00:12:16,680
on a bit of a whim to see
a friend on the promise

319
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:19,410
that he would help me to
restructure my business,

320
00:12:19,410 --> 00:12:20,940
from serving customers B2C

321
00:12:20,940 --> 00:12:24,900
to servicing other
businesses, B2B as well.

322
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:28,050
He taught me that by focusing
on selling to businesses,

323
00:12:28,050 --> 00:12:29,184
I could increase my numbers

324
00:12:29,184 --> 00:12:32,130
without having to deal
with so many people.

325
00:12:32,130 --> 00:12:34,680
This is known as the 80-20 principle.

326
00:12:34,680 --> 00:12:35,910
I learned that I could focus

327
00:12:35,910 --> 00:12:39,480
on the 20% of things that
produce 80% of my income.

328
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:42,330
I traveled abroad to China
and Japan where I learned

329
00:12:42,330 --> 00:12:44,700
about the idea of lean manufacturing,

330
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:47,100
which I related to my everyday life.

331
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:50,340
I started cutting anything
unnecessary outta my business

332
00:12:50,340 --> 00:12:52,470
and personal life so I could focus on

333
00:12:52,470 --> 00:12:55,350
what gave me the most meaning and results.

334
00:12:55,350 --> 00:12:58,620
Through this, I'd finally
achieved multimillionaire status

335
00:12:58,620 --> 00:13:01,410
but it felt kind of empty, and that's when

336
00:13:01,410 --> 00:13:04,320
I had a revelation that
changed my life forever.

337
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:06,720
Stage five, the revelation.

338
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:09,690
This is when I went to
$10 million and beyond.

339
00:13:09,690 --> 00:13:11,550
This brings me to where I am today.

340
00:13:11,550 --> 00:13:13,802
I thought about which
investments were most important

341
00:13:13,802 --> 00:13:17,490
to me in my life, and I realized
it was the relationships

342
00:13:17,490 --> 00:13:19,290
with my family and friends.

343
00:13:19,290 --> 00:13:22,530
You'll be the same person in
five years as you are today,

344
00:13:22,530 --> 00:13:25,800
except for the people you
meet and the books you read.

345
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:28,440
I started thinking about
how to pass the torch

346
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:31,140
and I taught my son Curtis about finance.

347
00:13:31,140 --> 00:13:33,120
We started this YouTube channel together

348
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:35,610
as a way to educate the younger generation

349
00:13:35,610 --> 00:13:38,880
from the perspective, not
of some rich influencer,

350
00:13:38,880 --> 00:13:40,950
but as a guy who did it with passion

351
00:13:40,950 --> 00:13:42,420
and a bit of elbow grease.

352
00:13:42,420 --> 00:13:45,600
I started spending more time
enjoying the little moments,

353
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:48,450
appreciating what I have
and what I've worked for

354
00:13:48,450 --> 00:13:50,880
and fostering quality relationships.

355
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:52,530
The final stage for a lot of people

356
00:13:52,530 --> 00:13:54,300
later in life is philanthropy.

357
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:56,880
Some people like Bill
Gates start foundations.

358
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:59,310
Others like Ray Dalio, write books.

359
00:13:59,310 --> 00:14:01,320
This is my form of giving back.

360
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:03,360
When I reflect on my journey getting here,

361
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:05,310
I'm proud of everything I've done.

362
00:14:05,310 --> 00:14:06,720
I still hustle hard,

363
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:09,660
but what is really meaningful
to me is being able to share

364
00:14:09,660 --> 00:14:12,330
my knowledge and inspire
a younger generation

365
00:14:12,330 --> 00:14:15,390
to go after their dreams
and achieve success.

366
00:14:15,390 --> 00:14:17,340
So I'm gonna leave the
next video right up there

367
00:14:17,340 --> 00:14:18,900
but don't click on it just yet.

368
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:21,390
Make sure to subscribe if
you wanna grow your wealth.

369
00:14:21,390 --> 00:14:23,373
Okay, I'll see you over there.

